{"id":"2011.00352","submitter":"Imed Zaguia","authors":"Maurice Pouzet and Imed Zaguia","title":"Graphs containing finite induced paths of unbounded length","comments":"28 pages, 3 figures","journal-ref":"Discrete Mathematics & Theoretical Computer Science, vol. 23 no.\n  2, special issue in honour of Maurice Pouzet, Special issues (March 8, 2022)\n  dmtcs:9124","doi":"10.46298/dmtcs.6915","report-no":null,"categories":"math.CO","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The age $\\mathcal{A}(G)$ of a graph $G$ (undirected and without loops) is the\ncollection of finite induced subgraphs of $G$, considered up to isomorphy and\nordered by embeddability. It is well-quasi-ordered (wqo) for this order if it\ncontains no infinite antichain. A graph is \\emph{path-minimal} if it contains\nfinite induced paths of unbounded length and every induced subgraph $G'$ with\nthis property embeds $G$. We construct $2^{\\aleph_0}$ path-minimal graphs whose\nages are pairwise incomparable with set inclusion and which are wqo. Our\nconstruction is based on uniformly recurrent sequences and lexicographical sums\nof labelled graphs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 31 Oct 2020 20:12:31 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 17 Nov 2020 17:59:50 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 4 Aug 2021 13:35:08 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 21 Feb 2022 14:33:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-14"}
